Yeah, that commit message is rough. Unfortunately, the issue is moot now — since we just switched to `manual-commit` strategy, Entire won't auto-create commits anymore. The bad messages were a side effect of `auto-commit` capturing whatever text happened to be in the agent's context.

There is an `auto-summarize` option that uses AI to generate better summaries, but it only applies to the auto-commit strategy:

```json
{
  "strategy": "auto-commit",
  "strategy_options": {
    "summarize": {
      "enabled": true
    }
  }
}
```

Since you're now on `manual-commit`, commit messages are entirely in your (and my) control — Entire just captures checkpoint metadata alongside normal `git commit` calls. So the real safeguard is the conventional commit format we already follow (`feat(scope): description`).

That particular commit on the PR — you may want to consider squash-merging that PR if you haven't already, so it collapses into a single clean message on `main`.
